Python code:
Method 1: Using if-else Statements 1
n=int(input())
if(n%400==0 or (n%100!=0 and n%4==0)):
    print("YES")
else:
    print("NO")
output:
1988--Yes
1700--No

Method 2: Using if-else Statements 2
n=int(input())
if(((n%4==0) and(n%100!=0)) or(n%400==0)):
    print("YES")
else:
    print("NO")
output:
1988--Yes
1700--No

Method 3: Using Calendar Module
import calendar
year=int(input())
if calendar.isleap(year):
    print("YES")
else:
    print("NO")
output:
1988--Yes
1700--No

CPP Code:
Method 1: Using if-else Statements 1
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int main()
{
    int year;
    cin>>year;
    if((((year%4==0) and (year%100!=0)) or (year%400==0)))
    {
      cout<<"Yes";
    }
    else
    {
      cout<<"No";
    }
    
}
output:
1988--Yes
1700--No



    
